doc.after: The Philippines has a simple literacy rate of 95.6%, with 95.1% for males and 96.1% for females. The Philippines has a functional literacy rate of 86.45%, with 84.2% for males and 88.7% for females in 2008.[368][369] Literacy in females is greater than in males.[368] Education spending accounts for 16.11% in the proposed 2015 national budget.[370][371]
